'''Shoe Wedges are wedge type Shoe Inserts that affix inside any footwear to make the user look taller.'''

They are manufactured using Eva Resin foam and are also called shoe inserts or shoe lifts in the UK.

They are used in all walks of life by men and women who wish to appear taller,look slimmer to others,or to correct a limb length discrepency in one foot.


The term 'shoe wedges' has become a mainstay in describing secret height increasing shoe inserts.
[http://www.celebheights.com]
[http://www.shoelifts.co.uk]
They typically come in sizes ranging from 0.25 to 3 inches. Users of larger sizes obviously need top use high topped type footwear to allow the secret height increasing insert to fit comfortably inside th users footwear.

Research shows that approx 5 million people on a daily basis wear Shoe Wedges in their footwear to appear taller.
[http://www.shoelifts.co.uk]

The origion of the term 'Shoe Wedges' can be attributed to the shape of the secret shoe insert. i.e. It looks like a wedge.
[http://www.shoelifts.co.uk]


Shoe Wedges are also used for limb length discrepency issues.